On Tue, Jun 29, 2004 at 02:10:13PM -0700, Sean Dorman wrote:
> I run a 4.12 RP in my Westy and I like it. Having a 3.88 in there
> with a stock 1600 would be a little too much (actually, not enough
> HP that is). I can run at 70MPH on flat land with no problems. 

I'll add a "here, here" to Sean's comment. I didn't want the 3.88 &
went with the 4.12. It's a nice ratio. The 4th is a bit tall (large
gap between 3rd & 4th) but not enough to worry. I cruise all day at 65
up/down TN,NC,VA hills and have NO problems. It's a good combo for a
stock/mild engine.


